proposalTitle: Allocate Budget for New Classroom Chairs and Fans
description:
Description:
This proposal suggests allocating funds from the school DAO’s improvement budget to purchase 50 ergonomic classroom chairs and 10 wall-mounted fans for [School Name]. This initiative aims to address the lack of seating and ventilation in classrooms, enhancing comfort and focus for students during lessons.

Key Details:

Problem:

Many classrooms lack sufficient chairs, forcing students to sit on the floor.
Poor ventilation makes the learning environment uncomfortable, especially during warmer months.
Proposed Solution:

Allocate $2,000 from the DAO improvement budget to procure ergonomic chairs and energy-efficient fans.
Install the chairs and fans in classrooms identified as high-priority during an initial survey.
Benefits:

Improved student comfort and engagement during lessons.
Enhanced focus and productivity in a more conducive learning environment.
Implementation:

Local vendors will be sourced through a competitive bidding process.
Purchases and installations will be overseen by the school’s facilities team.
Progress will be tracked and reported on the DAO platform.
